  "prompt": "How many national parks are in Gujarat?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, Gujarat has **four national parks**. These are:\n\n1. **Gir Forest National Park** - Famous for being the only natural habitat of the Asiatic lion.\n2. **Blackbuck National Park (Velavadar)** - Known for its population of blackbucks and diverse birdlife.\n3. **Marine National Park (Gulf of Kutch)** - India's first marine national park, renowned for its coral reefs and marine biodiversity.\n4. **Vansda National Park** - A small but ecologically rich park known for its dense forests and diverse wildlife.\n\nThese parks contribute significantly to Gujarat's biodiversity and conservation efforts.",
